Apple will host its annual National Parks Apple Watch activity challenge on Sunday, August 24. The event is designed to celebrate national parks across the United States.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/08/august-2025-national-parks.jpg" alt="" width="953" height="536" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1015218" /><br/>
Apple Watch owners can earn an Apple Watch activity award by doing a workout that lasts for 20 minutes or more on August 24, 2025. <br/>
<br/>
Like all of the Apple Watch activity challenges, earning the award will provide users with animated stickers that can be used in the Messages app. <br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/08/national_parks_2025_1.png?noresize" alt="" width="300" height="300" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1015219" /><br/>
<br/>
